HEADWORD: Improperia
<hw>Im`pro*pe"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.,
reproaches.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A series of antiphons and
responses, expressing the sorrowful remonstrance of our Lord with his
people; -- sung on the morning of the Good Friday in place of the usual
daily Mass of the Roman ritual.</def> <rj><au>Grove.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Improperly</ent>⟦br⟧
